        <updateDate>2021-08-19T13:54:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Innocent Party Protection Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires a federal court, under certain circumstances, to deny a plaintiff's motion to transfer a case to state court based on diversity of state citizenship among the parties. A court must deny such a motion if it finds, for example, that the plaintiff's claim against a defendant is implausible or is not made in good faith.<br /></p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
